Sentencas: Samarium doped cerium oxide (SDC) is widely investigated as an electrolyte material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) applications.
Titulo: Effect of iron oxide co-doping on structural, thermal, and electrochemical properties of samarium doped ceria solid electrolyte

Sentencas: However, the pristine SDC suffers from limited conductivity and stability.
Titulo: Effect of iron oxide co-doping on structural, thermal, and electrochemical properties of samarium doped ceria solid electrolyte

Sentencas: In this work, we prepare iron oxide (FeO) co-doped SDC electrolyte material via the solid-state method for SOFCs applications.
Titulo: Effect of iron oxide co-doping on structural, thermal, and electrochemical properties of samarium doped ceria solid electrolyte

Sentencas: The microstructural, thermal, and ionic conductivities of FeO/SDC electrolyte are investigated using X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscope (SEM), energy dispersive X-ray analysis (EDX), thermogravimetric analysis (TGA), and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) respectively.
Titulo: Effect of iron oxide co-doping on structural, thermal, and electrochemical properties of samarium doped ceria solid electrolyte

Sentencas: The XRD and SEM studies confirm that as-prepared electrolyte is single phase and dense homogenous structure respectively.
Titulo: Effect of iron oxide co-doping on structural, thermal, and electrochemical properties of samarium doped ceria solid electrolyte

Sentencas: The EIS analysis exhibits the highest ionic conductivity of similar to 0.147 S/cm at 600 degrees C along with power density similar to 552 mW/cm(2) and open-circuit voltage (OCV) 1.3 V in the solid oxide electrolysis cell.
Titulo: Effect of iron oxide co-doping on structural, thermal, and electrochemical properties of samarium doped ceria solid electrolyte
